data.description: Charming 1939 bungalow with coved ceilings, rounded archways, plus the original front door, woodwork, and floors in various parts of the home! Main floor has bedroom, bath, kitchen, and living room. The addition is currently used as an office but it is believed to have been a laundry room in the past. Renewal by Anderson windows were installed throughout the home in 2019. Downstairs is mostly wide open with an additional room and storage. It is also has a bathroom which does need repairs before being usable again. New sewer line installed within the last two years. Detached workshop/one-car garage with alley access. Fenced backyard. House does have some deferred maintenance, and buyer will need to purchase with cash or conventional loan.
